\begin_layout Title
Simplified model of a voltage driven unipolar atomic switch
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Ido Marcus
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
\noindent
Unipolar resistive switching was observed in Ag|PVP|Ag metal-insulator-metal
 interfaces.
 We suggest a simplified model that qualitatively captures the dynamics
 of filament formation
\backslash
dissolution at the interface.
 The model is intended to be used for simulation of electrical activity
 in a network of such atomic switches.
\end_layout

