 - above which cations migrate and gradually form a filament.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
When 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|V\right|>V_{\mbox{set}}$
\end_inset

, the direction of migration depends on polarity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The difference 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|V\right|-V_{\mbox{set}}$
\end_inset

 determines the rate of migration.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $V_{\mbox{reset}}$
\end_inset

 - under which the filament gradually dissolves.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
When 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|V\right|<V_{\mbox{reset}}$
\end_inset

, the filament dissolves regardless of polarity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The difference 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{\mbox{reset}}-\left|V\right|$
\end_inset

 determines the rate of dissolution.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The current state of a switch is represented in a variable 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 that has flux-linkage dimensions (
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\lambda\right]=\mbox{voltage}\cdot\mbox{time}$
\end_inset

).
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
This reflects the notion that filaments form
\backslash
dissolve over time due to the presence
\backslash
